commitResults.messageBody:
Changed name from Duke to Cortana to pay homage to one of my favourite games, Halo.
Cortana is the AI that assists the protagonist of the series, the Master Chief, in his missions.

Use Scanner library to collect inputs from the Command Line Interface(CLI)
Use while loop to continuously run until user inputs "bye" to end the bot
Create echo effect by printing out the input of the user
Use String variables to reuse strings

To prevent additional work from adding line into System.out.println statements
Instead of e.g System.out.println(line + greeting + line)
Now System.out.println(greeting)
Because String variable 'greeting' has already been edited to include the line

Create TaskList class to modularly build up list features.
Define Two methods: String add(String task), String display()

Create Task class to allow editing of done status easily as opposed to using a matrix
Add print statements to catch erroneous input for mark
Edit TaskList class to take in Task objects instead of String

Create 3 subclasses of Task: ToDos, Deadlines, Events
Update String parsing with split("/")
Update print statements to reflect more information like number of tasks in a list

commitResults.messageTitle: Update sub-class names to singular form
